        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 26 at 4:27PM MDT by NWS Grand Junction CO</headline>
        <description>At 427 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Halchita, or near Mexican Hat, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mexican Hat, Halchita, Bluff, and Tselakai Dezza.

This includes the following highways...
U.S. Highway 191 in Utah between mile markers 21 and 22.
U.S. Highway 163 in Utah between mile markers 14 and 41.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
